Name: Gown
Flavour: A cylindrical dress held up by straps over the shoulders, worn over a shirt.

Name: Tunic
Flavour: A long shirt, stopping just below the hips. A belt is fastened around the waist.

Name: Arrow
Flavour: Needed to use a bow. Skillfully made and balanced.

Name: Beads
Flavour: Beads on a string, a mnemonic device.

Name: Belt Hanging
Flavour: A token used to signify rank, given by an authority figure. Needs a justification to own.
Bonus Secondary: Does not stack

Name: Club
Flavour: A strong piece of wood carved roughly. Not sophisticated, but works.

Name: Flint & Steel
Flavour: Used for starting fires.

Name: Common Herbs
Flavour: Mint, nettle, thyme and fennel. Delicious.

Name: Pin
Flavour: A metal pin, used to fasten a dress.
Bonus Secondary: Once per long rest: One of the <knot>s you roll scores 2 instead of 1.

Name: Bronze Ring
Flavour: Bronze or iron, polished to a shine. Pretty when it catches the eye, and a useful store of value.
Bonus Secondary: Once per long rest: One of the <knot>s you roll scores 2 instead of 1.

Name: Sling
Flavour: An alternative to a bow for those that cannot afford arrows. Some prefer it.
Bonus Secondary: Reminder: For all ranged attacks (with any weapon), if you roll no <knot>s, the GM chooses your target.

Name: Totem
Flavour: Something meaningful to you. A reminder of your mission. Can be attached to another item in your inventory.

Name: Forearm Guard
Flavour: Leather wrapping, unsophisticated.
Bonus Secondary: Does not work with shield

Name: Lead
Flavour: Literally just a hunk of lead. Softens in the hand until it can be moulded around the knuckles.

Name: Heather Honey
Flavour: Rare, from the north, with mild psychoactive properties.
Bonus Secondary: Grants +1 creative, -1 disciplined, and -1 kind starting 1 hour after consumption, lasting for 4 hours.

Name: Mustard Seeds
Flavour: Chew on to increase focus and hold back exhaustion.
Bonus Secondary: Consume to gain +1 disciplined in your next check.

Name: Medical Salve
Flavour: Fennel, garlic, and nettle. Can be massaged into an affected area to provide relief, and acts as a mild antiseptic.
Bonus Secondary: One use only

Name: Royal Seal
Bonus Main: Reduce authority damage by 3, use once per long rest

Name: Blood Thickener
Flavour: Alder and curds. Chew to thicken the blood and prevent loss.

Name: Skinning knife
Flavour: Can be used as a weapon, but is not particularly effective.

Name: Hair wax
Flavour: Use to improve your appearence.
Bonus Secondary: Gain +1 charmer for the next few hours.

Name: Sharpened Ring
Flavour: Bronze or iron, filed to make a sharp edge.
Bonus Secondary: Once per long rest: One of the <knot>s you roll scores 2 instead of 1.

Name: Staff
Flavour: As simple as a long strong branch.

Name: Axe
Flavour: Very common, though not typically used for battle.
Bonus Secondary: Difficulty 2 check to remove from a wounded enemy

Name: Bow
Flavour: Made of string and flexible ash wood. Useful for hunting, if you don't have animals to rear.
Bonus Secondary: For ranged attacks, if you roll no <knot>s, the GM chooses your target.

Name: Craft Tools
Flavour: The tools (if any are needed) required to perform your craft.

Name: Brooch
Flavour: Worn at the shoulder or chest, carefully crafted bronze or iron. Often associated with a noble family.
Bonus Secondary: Once check per long rest: All <knot>s rolled score 2 instead of 1. Activate this before exploding dice.

Name: Dagger
Flavour: A simple dagger. Powerful, but requires you to first get close to an enemy.

Name: Mace
Flavour: A wooden pole with a metal sphere at the end, not often seen.

Name: Aphoran Needle
Flavour: An unusual needle that glows gently blue, but won't be threaded. Interesting, but useless.

Name: Niello Ring
Flavour: Bronze with inlays of black niello, etching intricate patterns.
Bonus Secondary: Once per long rest: One of the <knot>s you roll scores 3 instead of 1.

Name: Poppy Seeds
Flavour: When brewed into a tea can reduce pain and induce relaxation.
Bonus Secondary: Takes a short rest to prepare, grants +1 endurer, -1 attack and -1 evade for 4 hours.

Name: Comb
Flavour: Carved from ash. Sturdy, yet elegant.
Bonus Secondary: Takes a short rest to prepare, grants +1 charmer, for 4 hours.

Name: Hurley
Flavour: A carefully shaped stick of ash with a paddle at the end. Can be used as a club or to launch projectiles.

Name: Advanced Salve
Flavour: Garlic and pepper, antisceptic, cna provide muscle relief.
Bonus Secondary: One use only

Name: Bracelet
Flavour: Made from polished bronze.
Bonus Secondary: Once check per long rest: All <knot>s rolled score 2 instead of 1. Activate this before exploding dice.

Name: Instrument
Flavour: Typically a lyre, might also be a pan flute or drum.

Name: Shield
Flavour: A circular shield, painted with the colours of it's tribe.

Name: Spear
Flavour: A powerful multipurpose weapon. Useful in both close combat and when thrown.
Conflict Class: Melee - Attack / Melee - Defend / Ranged - Attack
Bonus Secondary: Difficulty 3 check to remove from a wounded enemy

Name: Writing Tools
Flavour: A quill and parchment. Parchment made from animal skin. Ink made from blood.

Name: Seax
Flavour: Somewhere between a sword and an axe. A single edged blade the length of your forearm.

Name: Whip
Flavour: Rope with a metal tip. Considered a dishonourable weapon.
Bonus Secondary: If you roll no <knot>s, the GM chooses your target.

Name: Beeswax ingot
Flavour: Smells good, raw material used in potions, food, candle making and many others.

Name: Earrings
Flavour: Bronze, bone, perhaps seashells.

Name: Necklace
Flavour: Carefully crafted from bronze or bone, fastened with string.

Name: Robes
Flavour: Similar to a toga, fastens at one shoulder. Worn by religious figures.

Name: Aphoran Spool
Flavour: An Aphoran artefact, glowing blue thread, incredibly strong, but cannot be threaded. Evaporates when cut away from spool.

Name: Braces
Flavour: Bronze wrappings around the forearm. Defensive. Also pretty.
Bonus Main: Once per long rest: <knot>s score 2 instead of 1. Activate before exploding.
Bonus 2: +2 Dice, Does not work with shield

Name: Fine Hurley
Flavour: Made from the base of an ash tree, near the roots. A smooth and flat "bas" at one end, shaped a bit like a foot in profile, is used to hit stones towards a target. Doubles up as a club.

Name: Noble Staff
Flavour: A staff with a symbol of office at its top. Doubles as a weapon.

Name: Helm
Flavour: Rusted and poorly fitting.
Bonus Secondary: -1 Damage from ranged attacks

Name: Old Sword
Flavour: An ancient metal sword, passed down through generations, could do with a clean.

Name: Sword of Ridderak Hal
Flavour: Appears as a regular old sword, but sets alight when drawn from it's sheath

Name: Fine Shield
Flavour: Light and strong, painted with the colours of it's tribe. With a steel rim and leather straps.

Name: Jeweled Ring
Flavour: Bronze with embedded glass beads, and a small polished piece of amber or amethyst.
Bonus Secondary: Once per long rest: One of the <knot>s you roll scores 4 instead of 1.

Name: Fragrance
Flavour: Delicate rosewater, with an earthy base. A common scent, but very effective.
Bonus Secondary: Consume to gain +2 charmer for the next 3 hours.

Name: Old Mirror
Flavour: Slightly rusted iron with a thin silver enamel. Good for adjusting your appearence.
Bonus Secondary: Use to gain +1 charmer for the next few hours

Name: Enamel Sheet
Flavour: Raw material used to make jewlery.

Name: Fine Belt
Flavour: Leather, with a metal buckle. Worn over a tunic or gown.

Name: Fine Gown
Flavour: Dyed in it's tribes colours, with embroidered patterns.

Name: Fine Tunic
Flavour: Dyed in it's tribes colours, with embroidered patterns.

Name: Ceremony Seax
Flavour: Wielded by druids, to be used in a ritual sacrifice.

Name: Large Shield
Flavour: In the Aphoran style, but smaller. 5 ft by 3, gently curved, with a slot through which a spear can be thrust.
Bonus Secondary: Roll 3 less dice on maneuvers and attacks using anything other than a spear. Take 3 less damage from all attacks from a chosen combat.

Name: Elkhide
Flavour: Raw material, quite rare. Used to make fine clothes.

Name: Incredible Salve
Bonus Secondary: One use only

Name: Mail Vest
Flavour: Slightly rusted. But still very valuable.
Bonus Secondary: -1 Damage from blades (but not arrows or spears)

Name: Fine Spear
Flavour: 6ft long, made from smooth ash with an iron head.
Conflict Class: Melee - Attack / Melee - Defend / Ranged - Attack
Bonus Secondary: Difficulty 3 check to remove from a wounded enemy

Name: Fine Bow
Flavour: Made from yew, a precious and flexible softwood. 6ft tall with metal string guards at either end.
Bonus Secondary: For ranged attacks, if you roll no <knot>s, the GM chooses your target.

Name: Gold Necklace
Flavour: Gilded and embossed with colourful enamel.

Name: Fine Pin
Flavour: A pin with a decorative head, displayed at the hip or shoulder.
Bonus Secondary: Once per long rest: One of the <knot>s you roll scores 5 instead of 1.

Name: Plain Sword
Flavour: A metal sword, with a simple leather hilt.

Name: Gilded Ring
Flavour: Silver over tin, or gold over bronze, embossed with intricate patterns. On the inside, the gilding has worn off, and the base metal can be seen.
Bonus Secondary: Once per long rest: One of the <knot>s you roll scores 5 instead of 1.

Name: Silver Mirror
Flavour: Polished and rust resistant.
Bonus Secondary: Use to gain +2 charmer for the next few hours

Name: War Horn
Flavour: Long and straight, made from Yew wrapped in brass bands, capable of overpowering sound. Cannot be used for drinking.

Name: Aphoran Knife
Flavour: A knife that glows gently blue. Stunningly beautiful, but completely blunt. Good for hanging on walls.

Name: Aphoran Salve
Flavour: Unkown ingredients. Pale white and translucsent. Instantly numbs the area it touched.
Bonus Secondary: One use only

Name: Noble Sword
Flavour: A sword to be proud of, tempered iron with a jeweled hilt and pommel.

Name: Silver Ring
Flavour: Pure and polished, studded with amethysts and enamel inlays.
Bonus Secondary: Once per long rest: One of the <knot>s you roll scores for 6.

Name: Fine Sword
Flavour: A steel sword, with a decorated bronze pommel and hilt.

Name: Fine Mail
Flavour: Clean, with minimal rusting. Extending to the elbows and knees.
Bonus Secondary: -2 Damage from blades (but not arrows or spears)

Name: Fine Bracelet
Bonus Secondary: Once check per long rest: All <knot>s rolled score 6 instead of 1. Activate this before exploding dice.

Name: Ornate Brooch
Flavour: Glittering silver, embossed with your tribe's symbol and studded with rare multi coloured gems.
Bonus Secondary: Once check per long rest: All <knot>s rolled score 6 instead of 1. Activate this before exploding dice.

Name: Gold Ring
Flavour: Glittering with amethysts and garnets, arranged in swirling, delicate pattern like drops of dew on flower petals.
Bonus Secondary: Once per long rest: One of the <knot>s you roll scores for 7.

Name: Brilliant Tunic
Flavour: Glowing blue thread makes intricate patterns on the sleeves, collar, and hem. A tunic fit for a royal.

Name: Brilliant Gown
Flavour: Glowing blue thread makes intricate patterns on the sleeves, collar, and hem. A tunic fit for a royal.

Name: Brilliant Robes
Flavour: Glowing blue thread weaves through in intricate abstract patterns. Overwhelming in its beauty, a gift from the gods.

Name: Brilliant Sword
Flavour: A shining sword, the pommel and hilt decorated with fine jewels.

Name: Agate Ring
Flavour: A single piece of rainbow quartz, carefully carved and polished into a heavy ring.
Bonus Secondary: Once per long rest: One of the <knot>s you roll scores for 8.

Name: Shillaly
Flavour: Walking stick / club. Made from knobbly blackthorn wood.

Name: Light Sword
Flavour: Thin and strong, made of hardened iron.

Name: Strong Axe
Flavour: Sharp and strong. A powerful weapon, if a little inelegant.
Bonus Secondary: Difficulty 3 check to remove from a wounded enemy

Name: Silver Spear
Flavour: Cannot be thrown back at you.

Name: Slippers
Flavour: Most Weal go barefoot, but shoes can be useful in circumstances

Name: Long Shanks Hamper
Flavour: Hamper with the ability to duplicate food items that ae left in it overnight

Name: The Giant's Cauldron
Flavour: Cauldron that boils meat very quickly but only for someone who is being honest
